    "read": [
      "Step 2 is a real burst but not a stable baseline. In every six-step gate, step 2 is materially faster than steps 4-6.",
      "Expandable allocator helps memory behavior but does not make full activation checkpointing sustain the burst. Full-AC plus expandable allocator still settles around 47.91 TFLOPs/GPU over steps 4-6.",
      "The likely causes are warmup/steady-state differences, activation-checkpoint recompute and autograd lifetime, and dynamic MoE owner-rank tail synchronization. The evidence is stronger for checkpointing and distributed backward tail effects than for allocator-only fragmentation.",
      "Future performance reporting should use late-step or multi-step averages, not a single step-2 number."
    ]
